{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

It is the peak of the [[Perseids|Perseid meteor shower]]. It is also known as the &quot;[[Glorious Twelfth]]&quot; in the [[United Kingdom|UK]], as it marks the traditional start of the [[grouse]] shooting season.

==Events==
*[[30 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Cleopatra|Cleopatra VII Philopator]], the last ruler of the [[Egypt]]ian [[Ptolemaic dynasty]], commits [[suicide]], allegedly by means of an [[Asp (reptile)|asp]] bite.
*[[1099]] &amp;ndash; [[First Crusade]]: [[Battle of Ascalon]]&amp;nbsp; Crusaders under the command of [[Godfrey of Bouillon]] defeat [[Fatimid]] forces led by [[Al-Afdal Shahanshah]]. This is considered the last engagement of the First Crusade.
*[[1121]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Didgori]]: the [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] army under King [[David the Builder]] wins a decisive victory over the famous [[Seljuk Turks|Seljuk]] commander [[Ilghazi]].
*[[1164]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Harim]]: [[Nur ad-Din Zangi]] defeats the [[Crusades|Crusader]] armies of the [[County of Tripoli]] and the [[Principality of Antioch]].
*[[1281]] &amp;ndash; The [[Mongol empire|Mongolian]] fleet of [[Kublai Khan]] is destroyed by a typhoon while approaching [[Japan]].
*[[1323]] &amp;ndash; Signature of the [[Treaty of Nöteborg]] between [[Sweden]] and [[Novgorod]] ([[Russia]]), that regulates the border between the two countries for the first time.
*[[1332]] &amp;ndash; [[Wars of Scottish Independence]]: [[Battle of Dupplin Moor]] &amp;ndash; Scots under [[Domhnall II, Earl of Mar]] are routed by [[Edward Balliol]].
*[[1480]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Otranto]]: [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] troops behead 800 [[Christian]]s for refusing to convert to [[Islam]].
*[[1499]] &amp;ndash; First engagement of the [[Battle of Zonchio]] between [[Republic of Venice|Venetian]] and [[Ottoman Turks|Ottoman]] fleets.
*[[1624]] &amp;ndash; The president of [[Louis XIII of France]]'s royal council is arrested, leaving [[Cardinal Richelieu]] in the role of the King's principal minister.
*[[1676]] &amp;ndash; [[Praying Indian]] [[John Alderman]] shoots and kills [[Metacomet]], the [[Wampanoag people|Wampanoag]] war chief, ending [[King Philip's War]].
*[[1687]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Mohács (1687)|Battle of Mohács]]: [[Charles V, Duke of Lorraine|Charles of Lorraine]] defeats the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottomans]].
*[[1793]] &amp;ndash; The [[Rhône (department)|Rhône]] and [[Loire]] (Lêre) ''[[Departments of France|départments]]'' are created when the former ''département'' of [[Rhône-et-Loire]] is split into two.
*[[1806]] &amp;ndash; [[Santiago de Liniers]] re-takes the city of [[Buenos Aires]] after the [[British invasions of the Río de la Plata|first British invasion]].
*[[1851]] &amp;ndash; [[Isaac Singer]] is granted a patent for his [[sewing machine]].
*[[1877]] &amp;ndash; [[Asaph Hall]] discovers the [[Mars]] [[Natural satellite|moon]] [[Deimos (moon)|Deimos]].
*[[1883]] &amp;ndash; The last [[quagga]] dies at the [[Artis Magistra zoo]] in [[Amsterdam]].
*[[1898]] &amp;ndash; An Armistice ends the [[Spanish-American War]].
*  1898   &amp;ndash; The [[Flag of Hawaii|Hawaiian flag]] is lowered from [[Iolani Palace]] in an elaborate annexation ceremony and replaced with the [[flag of the United States]] to signify the transfer of sovereignty from the [[Republic of Hawaii|Republic of Hawai`i]] to the [[United States]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the United Kingdom declares war on [[Austria-Hungary]]; the countries of the [[British Empire]] follow suit.
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; Alleged date of the first [[Philadelphia Experiment]] test on [[United States Navy]] ship {{USS|Eldridge|DE-173|6}}.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Waffen SS]] troops massacre 560 people in [[Sant'Anna di Stazzema]].
*  1944   &amp;ndash; [[Alençon]] is liberated by [[General Leclerc]], the first city in France to be liberated from the [[Nazis]] by French forces.
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; The [[Night of the Murdered Poets]]: 13 prominent Jewish intellectuals are murdered in [[Moscow]].
*[[1953]] &amp;ndash; [[Nuclear weapons testing]]: the [[Soviet atomic bomb project]] continues with the detonation of ''[[Joe 4]]'', the first [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[thermonuclear weapon]].
*  1953   &amp;ndash; The islands of [[Zakynthos]] and [[Kefalonia]] in Greece are severely damaged by an [[1953 Ionian Earthquake|earthquake]] measuring 7.3 on the [[Richter magnitude scale|Richter scale]].
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; ''[[Project Echo|Echo 1A]]'', NASA's first successful [[communications satellite]], is launched.
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[South Africa]] is banned from the [[Olympic Games]] due to the country's [[South Africa under apartheid|racist policies]].
*  1964   &amp;ndash; Charlie Wilson, one of the [[Great Train Robbery (1963)|Great Train Robbers]], escapes from [[Birmingham (HM Prison)|Winson Green Prison]] in [[Birmingham]], England.
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; Violence erupts after the [[Apprentice Boys of Derry]] march in [[Derry]], [[Northern Ireland]], resulting in a three-day communal riot known as the [[Battle of the Bogside]].
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; Between 1,000 and 3,500 [[Palestinian people|Palestinians]] are killed in the [[Tel al-Zaatar massacre]], one of the bloodiest events of the [[Lebanese Civil War]]
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; The first free flight of the [[Space Shuttle Enterprise]].
*  1977   &amp;ndash; The [[Sri Lankan riots of 1977]], targeting the minority [[Sri Lankan]] [[Tamil people]], begin, less than a month after the [[United National Party]] came to power. Over 300 [[Tamil people|Tamils]] are killed.
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of Peace and Friendship between Japan and the People's Republic of China]] is signed.
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; The [[1980 Montevideo Treaty|Montevideo Treaty]], establishing the [[Latin American Integration Association]], is signed.
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; The [[IBM Personal Computer]] is released.
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Mexico]] announces it is unable to pay its enormous external debt, marking the beginning of a debt crisis that spreads to all of [[Latin America]] and the [[Third World]].
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan Airlines Flight 123]] crashes into [[Mount Osutaka|Osutaka]] ridge in [[Gunma Prefecture]], [[Japan]], killing 520, to become the worst single-plane air disaster.
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; Canada, Mexico and the United States announce completion of negotiations for the [[North American Free Trade Agreement]] (NAFTA).
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Major League Baseball]] players go on [[1994 Major League Baseball strike|strike]]. This will force the cancellation of the [[1994 World Series]].
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; The [[Oscar class submarine]] [[Russian submarine Kursk|K-141 ''Kursk'']] of the [[Russian Navy]] [[Russian submarine Kursk explosion|explodes and sinks]] in the [[Barents Sea]] during a [[War exercise|military exercise]].
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Sri Lanka]]'s foreign minister, [[Lakshman Kadirgamar]], is fatally shot by an [[LTTE]] sniper at his home.
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; The [[bulk carrier]] [[MV New Flame|M/V ''New Flame'']] collides with the [[Petroleum tanker|oil tanker]] ''Torm Gertrud'' at the southernmost tip of [[Gibraltar]], ending up partially submerged.

