{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}  
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[293 BC]] &amp;ndash; The oldest known Roman temple to [[Venus (mythology)|Venus]] is founded, starting the institution of [[Vinalia#Vinalia Rustica|Vinalia Rustica]].
*[[1201]] &amp;ndash; The [[city]] of [[Riga]] is founded.
*[[1572]] &amp;ndash; [[Marriage]] in [[Paris]] of the future [[Huguenot]] King [[Henry IV of France|Henry IV]] of [[Navarre]] to [[Marguerite de Valois]], in a supposed attempt to reconcile [[Protestantism|Protestants]] and [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholics]].
*[[1587]] &amp;ndash; [[Virginia Dare]], granddaughter of [[governor]] [[John White (surveyor)|John White]] of the [[Colony of Roanoke]], becomes the first [[England|English]] child born in the [[Americas]].
*[[1590]] &amp;ndash; [[John White]], the governor of the [[Colony of Roanoke]], returns from a supply trip to England and finds his settlement deserted.
*[[1634]] &amp;ndash; [[Urbain Grandier]], accused and convicted of sorcery, is burned alive in [[Loudun]], [[France]].
*[[1636]] &amp;ndash; The [[List of signers of the Dedham Covenant|Covenant]] of the Town of [[Dedham, Massachusetts|Dedham]], [[Massachusetts]] is first signed.
*[[1783]] &amp;ndash; A [[Great Meteor of August 18, 1783|huge fireball meteor]] is seen across the [[United Kingdom]] as it passes over the east coast.
*[[1838]] &amp;ndash; The [[Wilkes Expedition]], which would explore the [[Puget Sound]] and [[Antarctica]], weighs anchor at [[Hampton Roads]] in [[1838]]
*[[1848]] &amp;ndash; [[Camila O'Gorman]] and Ladislao Gutierrez are executed on the orders of Argentine dictator [[Juan Manuel de Rosas]].
*[[1864]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Battle of Globe Tavern]] &amp;ndash; [[United States|Union]] forces try to cut a vital [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] supply-line into [[Petersburg, Virginia|Petersburg]], [[Virginia]], by attacking the [[Wilmington and Weldon Railroad]].
*[[1868]] &amp;ndash; French [[astronomy|astronomer]] [[Pierre Jules César Janssen]] [[Discoveries of the chemical elements|discovers]] [[helium]].
*[[1870]] &amp;ndash; [[Franco-Prussian War]]: [[Battle of Gravelotte]] is fought.
*[[1877]] &amp;ndash; [[Asaph Hall]] discovers [[Mars|Martian]] moon [[Phobos (moon)|Phobos]].
*[[1891]] &amp;ndash; [[1891 Martinique hurricane|Major hurricane]] strikes [[Martinique]], leaving 700 dead.
*[[1903]] &amp;ndash; [[Germany|German]] [[engineer]] [[Karl Jatho]] allegedly flies his self-made, motored gliding [[fixed-wing aircraft|airplane]] four months before the first flight of the [[Wright Brothers]].
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; [[Mayor]] of [[Tokyo]] [[Yukio Ozaki]] presents [[Washington, D.C.]] with 2,000 cherry trees, which [[William Howard Taft|President Taft]] decides to plant near the [[Potomac River]].
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; A [[Great Thessaloniki Fire of 1917|Great Fire]] in [[Thessaloniki]], [[Greece]] destroys 32% of the city leaving 70,000 individuals homeless.
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; The [[Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution]] is ratified, guaranteeing women's [[suffrage]].
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; The [[Thousand Islands Bridge]], connecting [[New York State]], [[United States]] with [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] over the [[St. Lawrence River]], is dedicated by [[U.S. President]] [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]].
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] orders a temporary halt to [[Nazi Germany|Nazi Germany's]] systematic [[Action T4|T4 euthanasia program]] of the [[mental illness|mentally ill]] and the [[Disability|handicapped]] due to protests.
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; The [[Australian cricket team in England in 1948|Australian cricket team]] [[Fifth Test, 1948 Ashes series|completed]] a [[1948 Ashes series|4&amp;ndash;0 Ashes series win]] over [[England cricket team|England]] during their undefeated ''Invincibles'' tour.
*[[1950]] &amp;ndash; [[Julien Lahaut]], the [[chairman]] of the [[Communist Party of Belgium]] is assassinated by far-right elements.
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[Vladimir Nabokov]]'s controversial novel ''[[Lolita]]'' is published in the United States.
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[American civil rights movement]]: [[James Meredith]] becomes the first black person to graduate from the [[University of Mississippi]].
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Operation Starlite]] begins &amp;ndash; [[United States Marines]] destroy a [[Viet Cong]] stronghold on the [[Van Tuong]] peninsula in the first major American ground battle of the war.
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; Vietnam War: the [[Battle of Long Tan]] occurs, when a patrol of [[6th Battalion, Royal Australian Regiment]] encounter the Viet Cong.
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; Vietnam War: [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] decide to withdraw their troops from [[Vietnam]].
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; In the [[Korean Demilitarized Zone]] at [[Panmunjeom]], the [[Axe Murder Incident]] results in the death of two US soldiers.
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Steve Biko]] is arrested at a police roadblock under the Terrorism Act No 83 of 1967 in [[King William's Town]], [[South Africa]].  He would later die of the injuries sustained during this arrest bringing attention to South Africa's [[apartheid]] policies.
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; Japanese election law is amended to allow for [[proportional representation]].
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Hurricane Alicia]] hits the [[Texas]] coast, killing 22 people and causing over [[USD]] $1 billion in damage (1983 dollars).
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; Leading presidential hopeful [[Luis Carlos Galán]] is assassinated near [[Bogotá]] in [[Colombia]].
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Wang Laboratories]] files for [[bankruptcy]].
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; A Federal jury finds the [[United States Environmental Protection Agency|US EPA]] guilty of discrimination against Dr. Marsha Coleman-Adebayo, under the [[Civil Rights Act of 1964]], later inspiring passage of the [[Notification and Federal Employee Antidiscrimination and Retaliation Act of 2002|No FEAR Act]].
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; Dennis Rader is sentenced to 175 years in prison for the [[BTK killer|BTK serial killings]].
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[2005 Java-Bali Blackout|Massive power blackout]] hits the [[Indonesia]]n island of [[Java (island)|Java]], affecting almost 100 million people.
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[President Of Pakistan]] [[Pervez Musharaf]] resigns due to pressure from opposition.

