{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1192]] &amp;ndash; [[Minamoto Yoritomo]] becomes [[Shogun|Seii Tai Shōgun]] and the ''[[de facto]]'' ruler of [[Japan]]. (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 12, 1192)
*[[1680]] &amp;ndash; [[Pueblo people|Pueblo Indians]] capture [[Santa Fe, New Mexico|Santa Fe]] from [[Spain|Spanish]] during the [[Pueblo Revolt]].
*[[1689]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Dunkeld]] in Scotland.
*[[1760]] &amp;ndash; The church (later [[cathedral]]) of &quot;Our Lady of [[Candlemas]] of [[Mayagüez, Puerto Rico|Mayagüez (Puerto Rico)]]&quot; is founded, establishing the basis for the founding of the city.
*[[1770]] &amp;ndash; [[James Cook]] formally claims eastern [[Australia]] for [[Kingdom of Great Britain|Great Britain]], naming it [[New South Wales]].
*[[1772]] &amp;ndash; King [[Gustav III of Sweden|Gustav III]] completes his [[coup d'état]] by adopting a new [[Instrument of Government (1772)|Constitution]], ending [[Age of Liberty in Sweden|half a century of parliamentary rule]] in [[Sweden]] and installing himself as an [[Enlightened absolutism|enlightened despot]].
*[[1808]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Vimeiro]]: [[United Kingdom|British]] and [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] forces led by General [[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington|Arthur Wellesley]] defeat [[Military of France|French]] force under Major-General [[Jean-Andoche Junot]] near the village of [[Vimeiro]], [[Portugal]], the first Anglo-Portuguese victory of the [[Peninsular War]].
*[[1810]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles XIV John of Sweden|Jean-Baptiste Bernadotte]], [[Marshal of France]], is elected [[Crown Prince]] of [[Sweden]] by the Swedish [[Riksdag of the Estates]].
*[[1821]] &amp;ndash; [[Jarvis Island]] is discovered by the crew of the ship, ''Eliza Frances''.
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[Nat Turner]] leads black slaves and free blacks in a rebellion.
*[[1852]] &amp;ndash; [[Tlingit people|Tlingit Indians]] destroy [[Fort Selkirk]], [[Yukon]] Territory.
*[[1863]] &amp;ndash; [[Lawrence, Kansas]] is destroyed by [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] guerrillas [[Quantrill's Raiders]] in the [[Lawrence Massacre]].
*[[1878]] &amp;ndash; The [[American Bar Association]] is founded.
*[[1879]] &amp;ndash; 1879 - The Virgin Mary, along with St. Joseph and St. John the Evangelist, reportedly appears to the people of Knock, County Mayo, Ireland.
*[[1888]] &amp;ndash; The first successful [[adding machine]] in the [[United States]] is patented by [[William Seward Burroughs I|William Seward Burroughs]].
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; The ''[[Mona Lisa]]'' is [[art theft|stolen]] by a [[Louvre]] employee.
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: The [[Second Battle of the Somme (1918)|Second Battle of the Somme]] begins.
*[[1928]] &amp;ndash; [[WRNY (defunct)|WRNY]] began regularly scheduled television broadcasts in New York City.
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; World War II: a [[Nazi]] flag is installed atop the [[Mount Elbrus]].
*  1942   &amp;ndash; World War II: the [[Guadalcanal campaign]]:  American forces defeat an attack by [[Imperial Japanese Army]] soldiers in the [[Battle of the Tenaru]].
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Dumbarton Oaks Conference]], prelude to the [[United Nations]], begins.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; Physicist [[Harry K. Daghlian, Jr.]] is fatally irradiated in a [[criticality incident]] during an experiment with the [[Demon core]] at [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]].
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]] signs an executive order proclaiming [[Hawaii]] the 50th state of the union. Hawaii's admission is currently commemorated by [[Hawaii Admission Day]]
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[Xa Loi Pagoda raids]]: the [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam Special Forces]] loyal to [[Ngo Dinh Nhu]], brother of President [[Ngo Dinh Diem]], vandalises [[Buddhist]] pagodas across the country, arresting thousands and leaving an estimated hundreds dead.
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; [[Soviet Union]]-dominated [[Warsaw Pact]] troops invade [[Czechoslovakia]], crushing the [[Prague Spring]]; on the same day, [[Nicolae Ceauşescu]], leader of [[Communist Romania]], publicly condemns the Soviet maneuver, encouraging the [[Romanian people|Romanian]] population to arm itself against possible Soviet reprisals.
*  1968   &amp;ndash; [[James Anderson, Jr.]] posthumously receives the first [[Medal of Honor]] to be awarded to an [[African American]] [[United States Marine Corps|U.S. Marine]].
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; An [[Australia]]n, [[Michael Dennis Rohan]], sets the [[Al-Aqsa Mosque]] on fire
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; A bomb exploded in the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]] campaign rally in [[1971 Plaza Miranda bombing|Plaza Miranda]], [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] with several anti-[[Ferdinand Marcos|Marcos]] political candidates injured.
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Operation Paul Bunyan]] at [[Panmunjeom]], [[Korea]].
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Philippine]] opposition leader [[Benigno Aquino, Jr.]] is assassinated at the Manila International Airport (now renamed ''[[Ninoy Aquino International Airport]]'').
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; Carbon dioxide gas erupts from [[volcano|volcanic]] [[Lake Nyos]] in [[Cameroon]], killing up to 1,800 people within a 20-kilometer range.
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Latvia]] declares renewal of its full independence after the occupation of [[Soviet Union]].
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[August Coup|Coup attempt]] against [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] collapses.
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Ruby Ridge Standoff]] in [[Idaho]]
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[NASA]] loses contact with the [[Mars Observer]] spacecraft.
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[NATO]] decides to send a peace-keeping force to the former [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslav]] [[Republic of Macedonia]].
*  2001   &amp;ndash; The [[Red Cross]] announces that a [[famine]] is striking [[Tajikistan]], and calls for international financial aid for Tajikistan and [[Uzbekistan]].
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Hurricane Dean]] makes its first landfall in [[Costa Maya]], Mexico with winds at {{convert|165|mph|0|abbr=on}}. Dean is the first storm since Hurricane Andrew to make landfall as a Category 5.

