==Deaths==
*[[1157]] &amp;ndash; King [[Alfonso VII of Castile]] (b. 1104/1105)
*[[1153]] &amp;ndash; [[Bernard of Clairvaux]], French theologian (b. 1090)
*[[1271]] &amp;ndash; [[Alphonse of Toulouse]], son of [[Louis VIII of France]] (b. 1220)
*[[1581]] &amp;ndash; [[Sakuma Nobumori]], Japanese retainer and samurai (b. 1527)
*[[1614]] &amp;ndash; [[Elizabeth Báthory]], Hungarian noble and alleged serial killer (b. 1560)
*[[1627]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacques Mauduit]], French composer (b. 1557)
*[[1673]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry Grey, 1st Earl of Stamford]], English soldier
*[[1689]] &amp;ndash; [[William Cleland]], Scottish poet and soldier
*[[1762]] &amp;ndash; [[Lady Mary Wortley Montagu]], English writer (b. 1689)
*[[1763]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Wyndham, 2nd Earl of Egremont]], British statesman (b. 1710)
*[[1796]] &amp;ndash; [[John McKinly]], American physician and President of Delaware (b. 1721)
