==Holidays and observances==
* Christian [[Feast Day]]:
** [[Æbbe of Coldingham]]
** [[Aredius]]
** [[Genesius of Arles]]
** [[Gregory of Utrecht]]
** [[Saint Joseph Calasanz|Joseph Calasanctius]]
** [[Louis IX of France]]
** [[Patriarch Menas of Constantinople|Menas of Constantinople]]
* Earliest date on which [[Tomatina|La Tomatina]] can fall, while August 31 is the latest; celebrated on the last Wednesday in August. ([[Buñol]])
* [[Public holidays in Uruguay|Independence Day]], celebrates the independence of [[Uruguay]] from [[Brazil]] in 1825.
* [[Opiconsivia]] held in honor of [[Ops]]. ([[Roman Empire]])
* [[Army_Day#Brazil|Soldier's Day]] ([[Brazil]])

